hm2WebHttpsCertFingerPrintType.name: hm2WebHttpsCertFingerPrintType
hm2WebHttpsCertFingerPrintType.description: Controls HTTPS certificate fingerprint generation. If set to 'sha1' hm2WebHttpsCertFingerPrint will show the SHA1 fingerprint of the certificate.

hm2WebHttpsCertFingerPrint.name: hm2WebHttpsCertFingerPrint
hm2WebHttpsCertFingerPrint.description: The HTTPS certificate fingerprint as hash. The type of the hash is defined with hm2WebHttpsCertFingerPrintType.

hm2WebHttpsServerRestart.name: hm2WebHttpsServerRestart
hm2WebHttpsServerRestart.description: Setting the object to restart will have the effect of restarting the HTTPS server. The server will load the new settings.

hm2WebHttpsServerTlsVersions.name: hm2WebHttpsServerTlsVersions
hm2WebHttpsServerTlsVersions.description: The TLS version supported by the HTTPS server. Changing the value has only effect after restarting the HTTPS Server.

hm2WebHttpsServerTlsCipherSuites.name: hm2WebHttpsServerTlsCipherSuites
hm2WebHttpsServerTlsCipherSuites.description: The cipher suite used by the HTTPS server. Changing the value has only effect after restarting the HTTPS server.

hm2TelnetServerAdminStatus.name: hm2TelnetServerAdminStatus
hm2TelnetServerAdminStatus.description: Enable/Disable telnet operation. A (1) enables, a (2) disables. When disabled, no telnet sessions are allowed by the system.

hm2TelnetServerPort.name: hm2TelnetServerPort
hm2TelnetServerPort.description: Telnet port operation. Default telnet port is 23. Setting the port to zero is not allowed.

hm2TelnetServerSessionsCount.name: hm2TelnetServerSessionsCount
hm2TelnetServerSessionsCount.description: Current number of active telnet sessions on this switch.

hm2TelnetServerMaxSessions.name: hm2TelnetServerMaxSessions
hm2TelnetServerMaxSessions.description: Maximum number of telnet sessions. An integer value from 1 to 5 specifies the maximum number of telnet sessions that can be established. The full range is not supported by all variants.

hm2TelnetServerSessionsTimeOut.name: hm2TelnetServerSessionsTimeOut
hm2TelnetServerSessionsTimeOut.description: Telnet login timeout (minutes) Config telnet timeout will set the telnet session timeout value. A session is active as long as the session has not remained idle for the value set. Specify a value from 0 to 160. Note: Changing the timeout value for active sessions does not become effective until the session is re-established.

hm2TelnetTrapEnable.name: hm2TelnetTrapEnable
hm2TelnetTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether login success, login failed or logout traps should be generated for this application.

hm2TelnetLastLoginInetAddressType.description: InetAddressType of the last login used for this application.

hm2TelnetLastLoginInetAddress.description: IP address or DNS name specified in the last request for this application.

hm2SshAdminStatus.name: hm2SshAdminStatus
hm2SshAdminStatus.description: Configures whether the SSH service is enabled on this switch. The default value is enable(1).

hm2SshProtocolLevel.name: hm2SshProtocolLevel
hm2SshProtocolLevel.description: Configures which protocol versions of SSH are enabled on this switch. Currently only SSHv2 is supported.

hm2SshPortNumber.name: hm2SshPortNumber
hm2SshPortNumber.description: The port number of the SSH server. Setting the port to zero is not allowed.

hm2SshSessionsCount.name: hm2SshSessionsCount
hm2SshSessionsCount.description: Current number of active SSH sessions on this switch.

hm2SshMaxSessionsCount.name: hm2SshMaxSessionsCount
hm2SshMaxSessionsCount.description: Max number of SSH sessions permitted on this switch. The full range is not supported by all variants.

hm2SshSessionTimeout.name: hm2SshSessionTimeout
hm2SshSessionTimeout.description: SSH idle timeout value for this switch in minutes. If the value is set to 0 the idle logout is disabled.

hm2SshKeysPresent.name: hm2SshKeysPresent
hm2SshKeysPresent.description: Indicates what key files are present on the device, if any.

hm2SshKeyOperStatus.name: hm2SshKeyOperStatus
hm2SshKeyOperStatus.description: Indicates what key files are currently being generated or deleted, if any.

hm2SshRSAKeyControl.name: hm2SshRSAKeyControl
hm2SshRSAKeyControl.description: Controls RSA key generation and deletion. Always returns noop(1).

hm2SshDSAKeyControl.name: hm2SshDSAKeyControl
hm2SshDSAKeyControl.description: Controls DSA key generation and deletion. Always returns noop(1).

hm2SshFingerPrintDSA.name: hm2SshFingerPrintDSA
hm2SshFingerPrintDSA.description: The local DSA fingerprint for SSH connections.

hm2SshFingerPrintRSA.name: hm2SshFingerPrintRSA
hm2SshFingerPrintRSA.description: The local RSA fingerprint for SSH connections.

hm2SshTrapEnable.name: hm2SshTrapEnable
hm2SshTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether login success, login failed or logout traps should be generated for this application.

hm2SshLastLogoutUserName.description: User name of last logout for this application.

hm2SshLastLoginUserName.name: hm2SshLastLoginUserName
hm2SshLastLoginUserName.description: User name of last login for this application.

hm2SshLastLoginInetAddressType.name: hm2SshLastLoginInetAddressType
hm2SshLastLoginInetAddressType.description: InetAddressType of the last login used for this application.

hm2SshLastLoginInetAddress.name: hm2SshLastLoginInetAddress
hm2SshLastLoginInetAddress.description: IP address or DNS name specified in the last request for this application.

hm2SshOutboundSessionsCount.name: hm2SshOutboundSessionsCount
hm2SshOutboundSessionsCount.description: Current number of active outbound SSH sessions from this switch.

hm2SshOutboundMaxSessionsCount.name: hm2SshOutboundMaxSessionsCount
hm2SshOutboundMaxSessionsCount.description: Max number of outbound SSH sessions permitted on this switch.

hm2SshOutboundSessionTimeout.name: hm2SshOutboundSessionTimeout
hm2SshOutboundSessionTimeout.description: SSH outbound idle timeout value for this switch in minutes. If the value is set to 0 the idle logout is disabled.

hm2PreLoginBannerAdminStatus.name: hm2PreLoginBannerAdminStatus
hm2PreLoginBannerAdminStatus.description: Enables/disables the NERC CIP-005-1 R2.6 compliant use banner

hm2PreLoginBannerText.name: hm2PreLoginBannerText
hm2PreLoginBannerText.description: The text added in this variable by the user will be displayed in the system login page as banner before login into the CLI (local or remote) or before login into the web interface. The default value is an empty string. Special meaning have the sequences '\t' and '\n' which allow the user to format the string with tabulator (\t) and newline (\n) format instructions. The use case is to provide a NERC CIP-005-1 R2.6 compliant use banner. The banner must be enabled using hm2PreLoginBannerAdminStatus

hm2CliLoginPrompt.name: hm2CliLoginPrompt
hm2CliLoginPrompt.description: Prompt string for the command line interface.

hm2CliLoginTimeoutSerial.name: hm2CliLoginTimeoutSerial
hm2CliLoginTimeoutSerial.description: Timeout for serial connections in minutes. If the value is set to 0, there will be no idle logout at all.

hm2CliLoginBannerAdminStatus.name: hm2CliLoginBannerAdminStatus
hm2CliLoginBannerAdminStatus.description: Enables/disables the display of the cli login banner text instead of the standard login banner.

hm2CliLoginBannerText.name: hm2CliLoginBannerText
hm2CliLoginBannerText.description: The text added in this variable by the user will be displayed in the system login page (local or remote) instead of the systemoverview. The default value is an empty string. Special meaning have the sequences '\t' and '\n' which allow the user to format the string with tabulator (\t) and newline (\n) format instructions. The Banner must be enabled using CliLoginBannerAdminStatus.

hm2ConsoleTrapEnable.name: hm2ConsoleTrapEnable
hm2ConsoleTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether login success, login failed or logout traps should be generated for console (V.24).

hm2ConsoleLastLogoutUserName.name: hm2ConsoleLastLogoutUserName
hm2ConsoleLastLogoutUserName.description: User name of last logout for this application.

hm2ConsoleLastLoginUserName.name: hm2ConsoleLastLoginUserName
hm2ConsoleLastLoginUserName.description: User name of last login for console (V.24).

hm2RmaTable.name: hm2RmaTable
hm2RmaTable.description: A list of management access entries (rules) to increase security.

hm2RmaEntry.name: hm2RmaEntry
hm2RmaEntry.description: An entry contains a rule for the management access.

hm2RmaIndex.name: hm2RmaIndex
hm2RmaIndex.description: The unique index used for each row in the RMA table.

hm2RmaRowStatus.name: hm2RmaRowStatus
hm2RmaRowStatus.description: Describes the status of a row in this table if it is active or not available.

hm2RmaIpAddr.name: hm2RmaIpAddr
hm2RmaIpAddr.description: Allowed IP address in IPv4 or IPv6 style.

hm2RmaPrefixLength.name: hm2RmaPrefixLength
hm2RmaPrefixLength.description: The length of the IP netmask.

hm2WebLoginSuccessTrap.name: hm2WebLoginSuccessTrap
hm2WebLoginSuccessTrap.description: This trap is sent if a user successfully grants access via web to the device. hm2WebLastLoginInetAddress contains the IP address or DNS name of the login request. hm2WebLastLoginUserName contains the user name of the last user who logged in into the device.

hm2WebLoginFailedTrap.name: hm2WebLoginFailedTrap
hm2WebLoginFailedTrap.description: This trap is sent if a user tried to grant access via web to the device. hm2WebLastLoginInetAddress contains the IP address or the DNS name of the login request. hm2WebLastLoginUserName contains the user name of the user who tried to login into the device.

hm2WebLogoutTrap.name: hm2WebLogoutTrap
hm2WebLogoutTrap.description: This trap is sent when a user logs out a web session. hm2WebLastLogoutUserName contains the user name of the last user who logged out of the device.

hm2TelnetLoginSuccessTrap.name: hm2TelnetLoginSuccessTrap
hm2TelnetLoginSuccessTrap.description: This trap is sent if a user successfully grants access via telnet to the device. hm2TelnetLoginLastInetAddress contains the IP address or DNS name of the login request. hm2TelnetLastLoginUserName contains the user name of the last user who logged in into the device.

hm2TelnetLoginFailedTrap.name: hm2TelnetLoginFailedTrap
hm2TelnetLoginFailedTrap.description: This trap is sent if a user tried to grant access via telnet to the device. hm2TelnetLastLoginInetAddress contains the IP address or the DNS name of the login request. hm2TelnetLastLoginUserName contains the user name of the last user who tried to log in into the device.

hm2TelnetLogoutTrap.name: hm2TelnetLogoutTrap
hm2TelnetLogoutTrap.description: This trap is sent when a user logs out a telnet session. hm2TelnetLastLogoutUserName contains the user name of the last user who logged out of the device.

hm2SshLoginSuccessTrap.name: hm2SshLoginSuccessTrap
hm2SshLoginSuccessTrap.description: This trap is sent if a user successfully grants access via SSH to the device. hm2SshLastLoginInetAddress contains the IP address or DNS name of the login request. hm2SshLastLoginUserName contains the user name of the last user logged in into the device.

hm2SshLoginFailedTrap.name: hm2SshLoginFailedTrap
hm2SshLoginFailedTrap.description: This trap is sent if a user tried to grant access via SSH to the device. hm2SshLastLoginInetAddress contains the IP address or the DNS name of the login request. hm2SshLastLoginUserName contains the user name of the last user who tried to login into the device.

hm2SshLogoutTrap.name: hm2SshLogoutTrap
hm2SshLogoutTrap.description: This trap is sent when a user logs out a SSH session. hm2SshLastLogoutUserName contains the user name of the last user who logged out of the device.

hm2ConsoleLoginSuccessTrap.name: hm2ConsoleLoginSuccessTrap
hm2ConsoleLoginSuccessTrap.description: This trap is sent if a user successfully grants access via console (V.24) to the device. hm2ConsoleLastLoginUserName contains the user name of the last user who logged in into the device.

hm2ConsoleLoginFailedTrap.name: hm2ConsoleLoginFailedTrap
hm2ConsoleLoginFailedTrap.description: This trap is sent if a user tried to grant access via console (V.24) to the device. hm2ConsoleLastLoginUserName contains the user name of the last user who tried to login into the device.

hm2ConsoleLogoutTrap.name: hm2ConsoleLogoutTrap
hm2ConsoleLogoutTrap.description: This trap is sent when a user logs out a console (V.24) session. hm2ConsoleLastLogoutUserName contains the user name of the last user who logged out of the device.

hm2MgmtAccessWebSESCertGenInProgress.description: Indicates that the certificate generation is already in progress.

hm2MgmtAccessWebSESCertNotPresent.description: Indicates that no certificate is available.

hm2MgmtAccessSshSESServerEnabled.description: Indicates that the SSH server is running.

hm2MgmtAccessSshSESKeyGenInProgress.description: Indicates that the SSH key generation is in progress.

hm2MgmtAccessSshSESKeyNotAvailable.description: Indicates that the SSH key is not available.
